This paper involves computer vision techniques such as deep learning for image recognition, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the use of crowd-sourced imagery and mobile contextual information suggests that it may also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-categories. The use of Wikipedia content and knowledge exchange suggests that it may also belong to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. Finally, the focus on urban environments and notable sites suggests that it may also belong to the cs.GR (Graphics) sub-category.
